column13: -Open. Low with several large branches on or bridging river downstream.  Small control feature below gauge pool appears different.  Control now appears to be small riffle approx 20m downstream.  River shows sign of high water event.  Lots of trees bent broken and piled up in tight corner upstream of gauge.  Lots of grass 1.5-2.0m above riverbed.  Unknown if this from 2023 or not.
column14: -FT2 wade.  Meaasured approx 100m upstream.  Very low flow lots of leaf debris in river.  Small cobble river bed.  Could affect the overall depths and area. -Cut taken in channel in line with gauge. Could not get solid bottom and site line to total station in gauge pool. Do not expect any slope difference given the low velocity and distance between spots of about 2m.  Reset at 15:32. New offset 8.135.  Could be a gauge correction will need to review this and past BM ties. Mid-section

column14: Returned for a confirmation mmnt as last mmnt plotted off the rating more than anticipated.  Flow Tracker did not warn of low SNR values the previous mmnt a few days earlier.  Measurement at Loon previous day was reporting low SNR values.  Flow Tracker also reported low SNR values during this measurement.  Suspect there could be an issue with the Flow tracker. Used telemetry from AQ for MGH.  -Cut taken in same spot as visit on 03OCT. Orientation of stadia rod created 0.02-0.03m pile-up of water on rod when trying to take cut. Had to still water with hands in front of rod to read without discrepancy between front and back of stadia. Mid-section
